The paper discusses the use of visual sensors for localization in domestic service robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively discusses the use of image matching algorithms and low light camera technology, which are sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for place recognition, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the analysis of performance, which is a common theme in machine learning and robotics research, and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of the proposed approach for domestic service robots, which is a sub-field of robotics (cs.ROBOTS).
